  "prompt": "How is the training in TCS?",
  "response": "TCS (Tata Consultancy Services) provides comprehensive training programs for new employees and existing staff. Here are some key aspects of training at TCS:\n\n1. Initial Training\n- Freshers undergo extensive induction and technical training\n- Programs cover technical skills, soft skills, and company processes\n- Training duration varies from 2-6 months depending on the role\n\n2. Technical Training\n- Role-specific technical training\n- Covers programming languages, tools, and technologies\n- Online and classroom training modules\n- Certification programs in various technologies\n\n3. Professional Development\n- Continuous learning opportunities\n- TCS Learning Management System (LMS)\n- Access to online courses and learning resources\n- Skill development programs\n\n4. Training Modes\n- Classroom training\n- Online/virtual training\n- Blended learning approaches\n- Self-paced learning\n\n5. Skill Enhancement\n- Domain-specific training\n- Soft skills development\n- Leadership programs\n- Project management training\n\n6. Global Exposure\n- Cross-cultural training\n- International project opportunities\n- Exposure to global work practices\n\n7. Certifications\n- Support for professional certifications\n- Reimbursement for relevant certification exams\n\nThe exact training experience can vary based on specific job role, location, and business unit.",
